docker compose up -d command is for downloading the Postgres image to your machine.
postgres Pulled
Docker finished downloading the Postgres image to your machine.

Network infra_default Created
Docker created a private network so containers can talk to each other.

Volume infra_mystore_pgdata Created
Docker created persistent storage for your database data.

Container mystore-postgres Started
Postgres is now running in the background.

----
Docker runs Postgres the database.
Spring Boot still needs a Java driver (JDBC) to communicate with it.

added a few dependencies like postgres and starter-jpa

Docker gives the database server. Maven gives Spring Boot the driver to talk to it.

